FIG. 1 is a schematic diagram showing a construction of a radiation thermometer embodying the present invention;


FIG. 2 is a schematic side diagram showing an arrangement of an optical member provided in the radiation thermometer;


FIG. 3 is a perspective view showing the optical member;


FIG. 4 is a side view of the radiation thermometer, a housing of the thermometer being partially cut away to show an interior construction of the radiation thermometer;


FIG. 5 is a diagram showing an optical image formed by a beam emitted from the radiation thermometer;


FIG. 6 is a block diagram showing a construction of a control system for controlling a light emitter and a motor provided in the radiation thermometer;


FIG. 7 is a timing chart of a motor drive signal, a detection signal of the optical member, and a drive signal of the light emitter;


FIG. 8 is a side view of the radiation thermometer;


FIG. 9 is a front view of the radiation thermometer;


FIG. 10 is a rear view of the radiation thermometer;


FIG. 11 is a perspective view showing an arrangement of an optical member of a first modified projector;


FIG. 12 is a block diagram showing a construction of a control system for controlling a light emitter and a motor provided in the first modified projector;


FIG. 13 is a diagram showing an optical image projected on a measurement object when using a first optical member variation which is formed with three through holes on the same circle;


FIG. 14 is a sectional view showing a configuration of a second optical member variation;


FIG. 15 is a perspective view showing an optical image projected on the measurement object when using the second optical member variation;


FIGS. 16A to 16E are diagrams showing a propagation direction of a beam light which changes as the second optical member variation is rotated;


FIG. 17 is a schematic diagram showing a construction of a second modified projector;


FIG. 18 is a schematic side diagram showing an arrangement of an optical member provided in the second modified projector;


FIGS. 19A and 19B are diagrams showing a configuration of an optical member provided a third modified projector;


FIG. 20 is a block diagram showing a construction of a control system of a second radiation thermometer provided with the third modified projector;


FIG. 21 is a schematic diagram showing a state of the second radiation thermometer that an optical system is set at a middle focal length;


FIG. 22 is a schematic diagram showing a state of the second radiation thermometer that the optical system is set at a telephoto limit focal length; and


FIG. 23 is a schematic diagram showing a state of the second radiation thermometer that the optical system is set at a wide-angle limit focal length.
